    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Protective headwear for tank crews, in a variety of designs since the advent of the tank as a modern war machine during WWI. Meant to protect against bumps and projectiles; more recent versions are provided with fixtures for the attachment of communication devices.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
